# Abstract

The rapid growth of online recruitment platforms has increased the number of fraudulent job advertisements. Fake job postings often aim to collect personal information or money from job seekers. This project proposes a machine learning and deep learning approach to detect fake job advertisements using the EMSCAD dataset containing 18,000 job postings. Various algorithms such as KNN, Decision Tree, SVM, Naïve Bayes, Random Forest, MLP, and Deep Neural Network (DNN) are evaluated. The DNN model achieved approximately **98% accuracy**, making it the best-performing classifier.

---

# Introduction

Online recruitment has simplified hiring but has also created opportunities for cybercriminals. Fake job advertisements can lead to financial loss and identity theft. Detecting fraudulent job postings using Artificial Intelligence improves recruitment security and protects job seekers.

